WEBVTT

00:04.226 --> 00:05.087
Welcome to Life Church.

00:05.487 --> 00:09.071
We're here to help you become who God created you to be, and we'd love to hear from you.

00:09.632 --> 00:15.618
Take a quick survey at life.church slash podcast connect to let us know how we can support you on your faith journey.

00:15.959 --> 00:17.300
And now let's go to the message.

00:22.646 --> 00:33.778
So this week as we start the new year and prepare our hearts to celebrate the goodness of God over 30 years, I've been doing a lot of reflecting over God's goodness

00:33.922 --> 00:35.366
in the past three decades.

00:36.168 --> 00:42.885
If you had asked me 30 years ago, what kind of church do you want to pastor?

00:43.847 --> 00:45.832
I would have told you a million things.

00:46.053 --> 00:46.654
I'm so excited.

00:47.116 --> 00:49.682
I would have said I want to pastor a mission-focused church.

00:50.210 --> 00:52.754
I want a vividly anchored church.

00:52.814 --> 00:56.640
I want an evangelistic church that reaches people far from God.

00:56.680 --> 00:59.945
I want a fast-growing church with people coming to Christ.

01:00.045 --> 01:01.828
Week after week, I want an innovative church.

01:01.848 --> 01:06.996
I want an influential church changing the city and maybe the state, maybe even the world.

01:08.077 --> 01:12.604
And if you ask me now, my answer would be similar, but it would be a little bit different.

01:12.624 --> 01:16.370
I still want all those things for God's church.

01:17.051 --> 01:18.834
But as of matured,

01:19.106 --> 01:25.074
a little bit over the last 30 years, and I've grown to know God more intimately.

01:25.114 --> 01:31.503
If you ask me now, above all else, what kind of church do you want to pastor?

01:32.304 --> 01:37.851
I would tell you, point blank, cleanly, clearly, in one sentence.

01:39.593 --> 01:44.240
I want to pastor a church that pleases God.

01:45.461 --> 01:49.106
Above all else, I want God to be honored

01:49.474 --> 01:54.660
The name of Jesus to be praised, and I wanna pastor a church that pleases God.

01:55.020 --> 01:59.285
And I wanna tell you a little bit of the story and take you with me and why I would say that.

02:00.346 --> 02:01.667
There's multiple layers to it.

02:01.807 --> 02:10.817
And one of the things is I've noticed over the years that many of you, maybe most of you, would be pretty sure that God loves you.

02:11.198 --> 02:12.139
We hope that you start there.

02:12.159 --> 02:13.620
You're pretty sure that God loves you.

02:14.201 --> 02:18.866
But many of you, you're not sure that God is always pleased with you.

02:20.130 --> 02:21.832
Because there's a difference, right?

02:23.174 --> 02:28.302
Than just being loved by someone and living in a way that pleases them.

02:29.343 --> 02:30.865
Raise your hand if you're a parent.

02:30.966 --> 02:31.767
Raise your hand if you're a parent.

02:32.147 --> 02:34.210
If online you can type in the comment section of my parent.

02:34.230 --> 02:36.373
If you're a parent you know exactly what I'm talking about, don't you?

02:37.114 --> 02:40.159
If you've got kids you know the difference between loving them and being pleased with them.

02:40.179 --> 02:48.050
I've got six children technically 12 now because they're all married and I love them all every single day.

02:49.250 --> 02:52.115
And I am pleased with them all every now and then.

02:52.175 --> 02:54.538
Right?

02:55.820 --> 03:01.529
I mean, we love our children all the time, but we're not always pleased with the decisions that they make.

03:01.590 --> 03:05.836
And the same would be true for God that God would love us every single one of us all the time.

03:06.437 --> 03:13.088
But there are times when we live in a way that pleases him and times that we live in a way that doesn't please him.

03:13.468 --> 03:17.074
And it makes me think of the moment that Jesus had that must have been

03:17.314 --> 03:23.502
indescribably intimate with his Heavenly Father, right after Jesus was baptized.

03:24.002 --> 03:30.570
In Matthew chapter three, verse 17, a voice from heaven, this is the Father, speaking to his son.

03:30.630 --> 03:40.082
The Father says, this is my son, publicly God declares the sonship of Jesus.

03:40.422 --> 03:46.610
And then he said, this is my son whom I love, but he didn't stop there.

03:47.170 --> 03:52.277
God the Father went on to say, with Him, I am well pleased.

03:52.998 --> 03:58.726
Not only do I love Him and I do, but I'm pleased with the way that He's living.

03:59.647 --> 04:01.610
So what kind of church do I want to pastor?

04:01.630 --> 04:06.696
Everything in me, I want to pastor a church that pleases God.

04:06.717 --> 04:14.807
That raises the question, if we're gonna be a church that pleases God, what kind of church pleases God?

04:15.468 --> 04:16.690
And the answer is,

04:17.410 --> 04:18.792
This is obvious, but here's the answer.

04:19.413 --> 04:25.061
A church that pleases God is made up of people who are pleasing God.

04:26.202 --> 04:27.264
Guess what that does for you?

04:27.324 --> 04:33.212
That puts you on the line with me to be a church that pleases God.

04:33.232 --> 04:35.335
It's made up of people, made up of you.

04:35.375 --> 04:43.186
If we're gonna be a church that pleases God, we have to live a life personally, individually and corporately that pleases God.

04:43.714 --> 04:53.924
So what I've done is I've done a detailed study of God's word and found what is in my opinion, perhaps the top five qualities in God's word of a church that pleases God.

04:54.024 --> 04:58.708
And we're gonna talk about one quality each week over the next five weeks, I'm gonna give you those qualities.

04:58.728 --> 05:00.350
What kind of church pleases God?

05:00.370 --> 05:05.074
Today, we're gonna talk about a reverent church pleases God.

05:05.494 --> 05:13.522
Next week, we're gonna talk about, we're gonna see in God's word that a faith-filled church pleases God because without faith, it's impossible to

05:14.402 --> 05:17.265
Please God, some of you have been doing your universe in Bible study.

05:17.706 --> 05:18.547
Good job.

05:19.127 --> 05:22.191
We'll shout it from the small group rooftops.

05:22.391 --> 05:23.392
You're in God's word.

05:23.893 --> 05:24.273
What else?

05:24.693 --> 05:28.077
A bold church pleases God.

05:28.378 --> 05:37.548
We're gonna see in week number four that a unified church is pleasing to God because Jesus prayed, Father, make them one as we are one.

05:37.868 --> 05:43.154
And finally, we're gonna see above any other quality, perhaps a loving church

05:43.330 --> 05:44.231
Please is God.

05:44.291 --> 05:45.373
What does it mean to love God?

05:45.393 --> 05:46.114
Is it tolerance?

05:46.174 --> 05:46.594
Is it love?

05:46.614 --> 05:47.536
Is it something different?

05:47.556 --> 05:49.158
We're gonna see what a loving church looks like.

05:49.478 --> 05:55.707
Today, I wanna come a little bit harder with a little more passion and a little more direct as we start a new year.

05:55.787 --> 05:56.688
Can I push you?

05:57.049 --> 05:58.571
If I can say you can, can I?

05:59.532 --> 06:00.033
You said it.

06:00.093 --> 06:00.513
Here we go.

06:00.533 --> 06:01.875
We're gonna talk about a reverent church.

06:01.895 --> 06:04.559
What is a reverent church?

06:04.579 --> 06:12.690
If you're taking a nose, a reverent church fears the Lord and lives with the sincere obedience

06:13.090 --> 06:13.470
to Him.

06:14.351 --> 06:26.363
A reverent church has a holy and a reverential fear of the Lord and lives with a sincere desire to obey and to please Him in all that we do.

06:26.603 --> 06:29.366
And we see it in His Word and Psalm 147.

06:29.946 --> 06:41.778
The Bible says the Lord delights in, the Lord is pleased with, the Lord delights in those who fear Him, who put their hope in His unfailing love.

06:42.242 --> 06:45.626
I want to show you what God's word says, but first I want to show you what it doesn't say.

06:46.186 --> 06:51.192
It doesn't say that the Lord delights in those who approach Him casually.

06:52.753 --> 06:53.955
He's the big guy upstairs.

06:54.575 --> 06:55.316
He's the big guy.

06:55.917 --> 06:58.239
He's not pleased with those who approach Him casually.

06:58.960 --> 07:05.527
He doesn't delight in those who serve Him comfortably or obey Him conveniently.

07:06.268 --> 07:12.114
Instead, the Lord delights in those who love Him with the reverent

07:12.386 --> 07:12.706
Fear.

07:13.327 --> 07:16.472
Now, culturally today, like, I don't want to be afraid of God.

07:16.532 --> 07:18.515
What does it mean to fear the Lord?

07:19.016 --> 07:24.144
It doesn't mean to be afraid of God like you're going to do something wrong and he gets you and smush you like a bug.

07:24.164 --> 07:26.487
That's not what the fear of the Lord means.

07:27.028 --> 07:31.735
In fact, the word fear in this text comes from the Hebrew word yare.

07:32.256 --> 07:38.265
And this word means very directly, it means fearing or awe, A.W.E.

07:38.285 --> 07:41.810
All filled reverently aware

07:43.394 --> 07:46.977
of God's holiness and authority.

07:48.219 --> 07:56.666
It's this deep sense of the holiness, the goodness, the righteousness, the glory, the power of God.

07:57.627 --> 07:58.728
And we are not Him.

07:59.769 --> 08:02.752
He is holy and set apart.

08:02.772 --> 08:09.599
So holy is He that we can't even stand in the purity of His presence and live.

08:09.619 --> 08:11.861
That's how holy He is.

08:12.201 --> 08:13.202
It's a reverent

08:13.570 --> 08:19.437
fear of a holy and a righteous and a good and a loving and a just God.

08:20.117 --> 08:21.839
It's the fear of the Lord, it's reverence.

08:21.879 --> 08:22.941
Now, what does this mean?

08:23.321 --> 08:33.953
Reverence for God isn't a fear that drives us away from God, but it's an awe that draws us to Him.

08:35.014 --> 08:42.002
It's the sense that He alone is worthy of our praise.

08:43.266 --> 08:47.691
He alone is worthy of our lives.

08:47.711 --> 08:54.439
He alone is worthy of our first and our best, our gifts to use for him.

08:54.979 --> 08:57.623
He should be the first thing on my mind when I wake up in the day.

08:57.863 --> 09:00.946
He should be the first one I wanna please when I go through my life.

09:00.966 --> 09:07.234
He alone is worthy of everything in my heart to give to him for his glory.

09:07.294 --> 09:11.058
So what I wanna do is I'm gonna push you a little bit and ask you what may be

09:11.330 --> 09:13.853
The most important question is we move into a new year.

09:14.253 --> 09:19.119
And I'm not gonna ask you what you may think, like what do you believe about God?

09:19.300 --> 09:21.502
I'm gonna ask you a deeper and more important question.

09:21.742 --> 09:27.690
And what I wanna do is I wanna ask you, what does your life say you believe about God?

09:28.991 --> 09:30.533
What is your life, your actions?

09:31.614 --> 09:38.162
If you just look at your last week, what does the way you live say that you prioritize?

09:40.226 --> 09:47.834
When you think about what you think about, what do your thoughts say is most important to you?

09:48.675 --> 09:57.483
When you look at how you spend your time, your money, who you hang out with, what makes you excited when you get really good news, what's the best news you could get?

09:57.543 --> 10:00.066
Is it something that's God honoring them or self-focused?

10:01.007 --> 10:07.954
Not what do you believe about God, but what does the way that you live say that you believe

10:08.098 --> 10:09.580
about God, why does it matter?

10:09.700 --> 10:14.947
It matters because how you view God determines how you live.

10:16.149 --> 10:21.876
How you think about him determines how seriously you reflect what he says.

10:22.197 --> 10:25.301
And so again, I'm gonna push you a little bit and I just want you to think about this.

10:25.862 --> 10:30.148
Do you take him seriously?

10:32.571 --> 10:34.994
Or do you treat God casually?

10:36.258 --> 10:43.309
I had a seminary teacher years ago that he called it a high view of God or a low view of God.

10:44.070 --> 10:50.880
Do you have a high view of God and his word, an elevated view that you place authority on it?

10:51.942 --> 10:54.386
Or do you have a reverent view of God?

10:54.726 --> 10:57.931
Or do you have a low view, a casual view?

10:58.031 --> 10:59.213
Jesus, I'm a home boy.

10:59.233 --> 11:01.857
Yeah, I read a Bible every now and then.

11:01.897 --> 11:03.059
I mean, the parts of it that I like.

11:03.320 --> 11:04.882
Did you have a high view of God?

11:04.994 --> 11:05.995
or a low view of God.

11:06.036 --> 11:11.524
And what I want to do is I want to show you very directly a contrasting view of a high and a low view of God.

11:11.544 --> 11:12.906
We'll start with a low view of God.

11:13.306 --> 11:18.233
When you have a low view of God, you take his word casually.

11:19.736 --> 11:29.650
If you read it, you may not take it seriously, you may debate it, you may obey the parts you like and not the other parts, or you don't even value it.

11:29.890 --> 11:30.311
at all.

11:30.631 --> 11:32.273
You treat God's Word casually.

11:32.653 --> 11:37.659
Second thing is you ignore conviction and rationalize sin.

11:37.679 --> 11:47.171
If there's something in your life that you know is contrary to God's Word, you may say, well, this is just the way I am and this is just by one thing.

11:47.231 --> 11:51.476
It's not that big a deal and this is my truth anyway and it's none of your business, what I do.

11:51.917 --> 11:54.880
And you rationalize sin and continue to live in it.

11:55.181 --> 11:59.666
And then finally, you know what God says, but you just do

11:59.970 --> 12:01.351
whatever you want.

12:01.471 --> 12:02.833
It's a low view of God.

12:03.433 --> 12:10.420
Contrast that with a high and a reverent view, a reverential fear in awe of the goodness of God.

12:10.440 --> 12:14.884
When you have a high view of God, you take his word seriously.

12:15.745 --> 12:19.569
It's not just a part of your life, it's the truth that guides your life.

12:20.330 --> 12:21.290
You're in it all the time.

12:21.971 --> 12:29.138
Not because you feel like you have to do it to please him, but because you want to know him through his word, it's living,

12:29.314 --> 12:35.642
It feeds you, it empowers you, it convicts you, it teaches you, it guides you, it conforms you to the image of Christ.

12:35.842 --> 12:40.649
It renews your mind so you're not bought into the lives of this world.

12:41.289 --> 12:42.751
You take this word seriously.

12:43.052 --> 12:45.915
You also repent of your sins quickly.

12:46.756 --> 12:49.840
When you do something wrong, you say, oh, God, I'm sorry.

12:50.421 --> 12:51.122
God forgive me.

12:51.330 --> 12:53.333
and then you turn away and you walk away from it.

12:53.353 --> 12:58.180
You don't live in it, you don't rationalize it, you don't make light of it, you repent and you turn quickly.

12:58.481 --> 13:21.234
And then finally, you obey God with reverence, no matter the cost, no matter what they say about you at school, no matter if they laugh at you, no matter if they talk behind you, back at work, no matter if they say, you're a religious freak, you're another, no matter if your girlfriend breaks up with you because you won't do the things she wants you to do,

13:21.890 --> 13:30.081
No matter the cost you say, because I have a reverent view of God in His Word, I want to obey Him no matter what.

13:30.141 --> 13:46.443
The reason I'm starting the year here and the reason I'm bringing the heat, maybe just a little bit more than normal, is because this is one of my biggest concerns as I look at culture and not just culture but as I look at the church, the church, our church.

13:46.463 --> 13:49.106
It's not that people don't believe in God, a lot of people do.

13:50.050 --> 13:52.633
but it's that people believe in Him without revering Him.

13:54.656 --> 13:57.180
And it creates what we could call a cultural Christian.

13:58.441 --> 14:06.492
This is someone who, who like, I'm a Christian, because I'm born into USA and, you know, I'm a nice guy and I'm killed in your body and stuff like that.

14:07.413 --> 14:11.679
And it's not that you've rejected God, you've just reduced Him.

14:14.042 --> 14:16.946
You've got a faith that's become way too familiar.

14:18.114 --> 14:26.286
And whenever your faith becomes familiar, you start to treat Jesus like he's no big deal.

14:26.306 --> 14:28.009
No big deal.

14:28.029 --> 14:31.414
That's baptized, I say, yeah, yeah, I do the church thing every now.

14:31.474 --> 14:32.476
I'll watch church online.

14:32.856 --> 14:34.779
Yeah, I'll pick up the Bible every now and then.

14:34.799 --> 14:36.221
Yeah, I'll do a good deed every now and then.

14:40.868 --> 14:44.594
But it's not the consuming desire of my heart to please him.

14:48.450 --> 14:54.860
There's one of the most powerful stories of familiarity with Jesus in Luke chapter seven.

14:55.601 --> 15:00.890
There's a Pharisee, an important educated religious leader named Simon.

15:01.511 --> 15:02.773
He said, Jesus, come over to my house.

15:03.073 --> 15:04.195
I'll throw you a fancy party.

15:04.595 --> 15:07.540
We're gonna have a great big party, a formal dinner.

15:07.560 --> 15:13.810
And so Jesus was there and there were some other Pharisees looking very phariseical, looking very holy.

15:14.658 --> 15:18.863
Some of you do when you walk in a church, like, oh, I'm in the presence of God here today.

15:18.963 --> 15:20.345
I'm going to be in the church that helps the God.

15:20.645 --> 15:22.928
They're looking at holy and such.

15:23.408 --> 15:28.154
And Jesus was there with them, but they treated him casually.

15:29.956 --> 15:34.481
When you walked into a first century home, there were these customs, kind of like today.

15:34.501 --> 15:39.887
If you came over to my house and I'm being polite to you, I'm honoring you.

15:39.907 --> 15:40.308
