18:08.037 --> 18:22.173
And they thought to themselves, if Jesus knew what kind of woman she was, he would call her out and not even let her sinfulness get close to his so-called holiness.

18:23.695 --> 18:28.040
And in Luke chapter seven, verse 44, here's what Jesus said.

18:29.522 --> 18:30.963
Jesus said, I came into your house.

18:32.725 --> 18:33.426
You didn't,

18:34.274 --> 18:42.723
give me any water for my feet, but she wet my feet with her tears and wiped them with her hair.

18:44.145 --> 18:50.352
You didn't give me a kiss, but this woman from the time I entered has not stopped kissing my feet.

18:52.614 --> 19:00.603
You didn't put oil on my head, but she's poured perfume on my feet as an act of worship.

19:00.623 --> 19:01.224
Think about it.

19:02.545 --> 19:03.186
Jesus,

19:04.290 --> 19:09.837
in the room, same Jesus, to entirely different responses.

19:11.760 --> 19:20.070
The Pharisees treated him as common, ordinary, no big deal.

19:22.834 --> 19:25.197
